fields.description:
In debugging an issue with the CC I found that the httpd-cc_error_log had grown to over 3GB. This file should probably be added to the same log rolling rules as the cc.log:

{code}
[root@eucahost-51-112 eucalyptus]# ll httpd-cc_error_log
-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 3631482791 Oct 22 20:50 httpd-cc_error_log
[root@eucahost-51-112 eucalyptus]# 
{code}

comments.body:
Seems the best, simplest workaround for when this file becomes excessively large is not to directly remove it (which causes logging to that file to stop unless httpd is sent a SIGHUP), but rather to truncate it in place:

{quote}
cp /dev/null $EUCALYPTUS/var/log/eucalyptus/httpd-cc_error_log
{quote}

The last issues with make install should have been resolved. For logrotate to work with our build from source test suite, the test must link the $EUCALYPTUS/etc/logrotate.d/eucalyptus file to /etc/logrotate.d/eucalyptus.

{noformat}
ln -sf $EUCALYPTUS/etc/logrotate.d/eucalyptus /etc/logrotate.d/eucalyptus
{noformat}
